cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for automatic classification of medical images, specifically for cardiac diseases associated with structural remodeling. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning models also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of 3D convolutional generative models, which suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
